<subSubSection id="C344BFE3CD39FFF0FF0CFD1AFC461DF2" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD39FFF0FF0CFD1AFC621AD2" blockId="13.[151,1437,356,1751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FF0CFD1AFE271A43" bold="true" box="[199,455,752,778]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. Distinguished from the nominotypical subspecies by its even brighter body coloration (
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD39FFF0FF6BFCFEFF111A66" box="[160,241,788,815]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,189,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[151,1435,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26–28. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) levigatum, habitat. 26–27—P. (B.) l. levigatum W. Horn. 26—♁, 15.6 mm, Amboaniho, ST (SDEI); 27—♁, 15.3 mm, Marotaonala (CCJM); 28—P. (B.) l. lucens Rivalier, ♀, 15.5 mm, Île de Beraphia, LT (MNHN). Bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506142/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) and following features: elytra metallic blue or green-blue, often with golden lustre on elytral disc; elytral punctures shallower and with wider and flatter, notably shiny intervals; setal vesture predominantly whitish; lacinia paler with ochre-testaceous outer area; antennomeres 6–11 brownish. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1365F0EDCD39FFF0FBD2FCB6FB791A3E" box="[1049,1177,860,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,187,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Pogonostoma (Bathypogonum) levigatum. 39–42— P. (B.) l. levigatum W. Horn. 39–40—pronotum: 39—♁, Marotaonala (CCJM); 40—♀, Vohemar (CCJM ex APCA); 41–44—male aedeagus or its apex: 41—showing internal sac, Ma- rotaonala; 42—ditto, dorsal view; 43–44—P. (B.) l. lucens Rivalier. 43—Ramena River (SDEI); 44—ditto, dorsal view. Bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506146/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Figs 44–43</figureCitation>
) shaped generally as in the nominotypical subspecies with variably longer or shorter apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD39FFF0FF0CFC4FFE041AAA" blockId="13.[151,1437,356,1751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
For the detailed redescription and illustrations of other characters, including of the 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD39FFF0FB93FC4EFB221AF7" box="[1112,1218,932,958]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">lectotype</typeStatus>
, see the monograph of the genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FEE4FC23FE381AAA" author="Moravec, J." box="[303,472,969,995]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD39FFF0FF0CFC06FC461DF2" blockId="13.[151,1437,356,1751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FF0CFC06FEA71D4F" bold="true" box="[199,327,1004,1030]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Variability</emphasis>
. Besides the rather variable coloration, also the length of the aedeagus apex considerably varies. As discussed and illustrated previously (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FDA2FBFBFCF31D62" author="Moravec, J." box="[617,787,1041,1067]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
, figs 278–284), the specimens from Ramena, Bealanana and “Tananarive”, arranged in SDEI under the unpublished name “ 
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FC4FFBDEFBED1D07" box="[900,1037,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">levipunctum</emphasis>
“ as well as the seven specimens in MFNB, show a considerable variability in the shape of the aedeagus apex. Nevertheless, as intermediate shapes of the aedeagi were found within the examined adults (also from the same locality), the differences in the length of the aedeagus apex were considered as a mere variability (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FD3AFB4BFC7A1DF2" author="Moravec, J." box="[753,922,1185,1211]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344BFE3CD39FFF0FF0CFB2EFBEF1F6B" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD39FFF0FF0CFB2EFBEF1F6B" blockId="13.[151,1437,356,1751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FF0CFB2EFE091D97" bold="true" box="[199,489,1220,1247]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Distribution and biology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E97EBCD39FFF0FE3DFB2FFCB21D96" authority="" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" box="[502,850,1220,1247]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bathypogonum">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FE3DFB2FFD701D97" box="[502,656,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FD6BFB2EFCAA1D97" box="[672,842,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Bathypogonum</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FC93FB2EFC551D97" box="[856,949,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">l. lucens</emphasis>
is considered a geographical subspecies described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FEDBFB02FE5B1C4A" author="Rivalier, E." box="[272,443,1256,1283]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref9106" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier (1970)</bibRefCitation>
from Sambirano. Besides the 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD39FFF0FCC0FB03FCDB1C4A" box="[779,827,1257,1283]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">type</typeStatus>
locality, the western near-shore island of Nosy Berafia (= Île de Beraphia) of the Radama archipelago, it occurs also in the area of the Ramena river south-east of Ambanja, both localities belong to western Sambirano. One examined specimen is labelled “Bealanana”, which is a district in an inland northern 
<collectingCountry id="F349ACF8CD39FFF0FEA2FABEFE121C27" box="[361,498,1364,1390]" name="Madagascar" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, but its northern border is adjacent to the district of Ambanja; thus the specimen may come from a forest in northern areas of the district, in the past probably connected by a forest strip running from the area of Ambondrona (southern part of the large Tsaratanana massif, Sambirano). The labels “ 
<collectingRegion id="499A228ACD39FFF0FB3FFA76FA721CFF" box="[1268,1426,1436,1462]" country="Madagascar" name="Antananarivo" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Antananarivo</collectingRegion>
” and “Tananarive” are either erroneous or more probably meaning “ 
<collectingCountry id="F349ACF8CD39FFF0FC4EFA2AFBF41C93" box="[901,1044,1472,1498]" name="Madagascar" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
”, as commonly labelled as such by insect dealers. The numerous specimens in MFNB, labelled “ 
<collectingCountry id="F349ACF8CD39FFF0FC9BFA0EFC3F1CB7" box="[848,991,1508,1534]" name="Madagascar" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
”, possess quite homogenous characters and belong probably to one population, although their exact origin is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344BFE3CD39FFF0FF0CF9C7FE001F9E" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1EC68CD39FFF0FF0CF9C7FE001F9E" blockId="13.[151,1437,356,1751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis id="B92A307ACD39FFF0FF0CF9C7FED41F0E" bold="true" box="[199,308,1581,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FE89F9C6FE0D1F0E" author="Rivalier, E." box="[322,493,1580,1607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref9106" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier (1970)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that he described this subspecies according to one male and two females. However, only the two females coming from the type locality were found in MNHN by the second author of the present paper (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FEA0F99FFDF31FC6" author="Moravec, J." box="[363,531,1653,1679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
); fortunately, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FD64F99EFCBB1FC6" author="Rivalier, E." box="[687,859,1652,1679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" pagination="269 - 338" refId="ref9106" refString="Rivalier, E. (1970) Le genre Pogonostoma (Col. Cicindelidae). Revision avec description d'especes nouvelles. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, New Series, 6, 269 - 338." type="journal article" year="1970">Rivalier (1970)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the aedeagus (of the missing male) was identical with that of the nominotypical subspecies. Consequently, one of the existing females was designated as 
<typeStatus id="54E552CACD39FFF0FF7DF956FEFD1F9F" box="[182,285,1724,1750]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF9199CD39FFF0FEE0F957FE341F9E" author="Moravec, J." box="[299,468,1725,1751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" refId="ref8440" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
